On Thu, 15 Nov 2001, Chris Mills wrote:

> Is it similar to the early, early Fords which circulated water based on the
> density or temperature of the water?
>
> Been a long time since I read something about that.

Yes.  The idea works if the radiator is above the engine and the lines
have a straight shot to the top of the radiator.  No ups and down allowed.
It isn't the most efficient way to dissipate heat, which is why cars soon
developed water pumps.

George Lyle

